<tt>elogv</tt> is a curses-based simple tool that parses the contents of elogs created by Portage.

== Installation ==

Install <tt>elogv</tt>:

{{emerge|app-portage/elogv}}

== Configuration ==

To use <tt>elogv</tt>, the Portage elog system needs to be configured in {{Path|etc/portage/make.conf}} with the following addition:

{{FileBox|filename=[[:/etc/portage/make.conf]]|lang=bash|1=
# Logging
PORTAGE_ELOG_CLASSES="warn error log"
PORTAGE_ELOG_SYSTEM="save"
}}

For additional variables, see {{Path|/usr/share/portage/config/make.conf.example}}.

{{Note|If the <code>PORT_LOGDIR</code> variable is unset in {{Path|etc/portage/make.conf}}, logs will be saved to {{Path|/var/log/portage/elog}} by default.}}

== Usage ==

To use <tt>elogv</tt>, type in a console:

{{Cmd|elogv}}
